		"description": "<p>You conjure a swirling flood of water. The water must be on the ground or in a body of water; if it is on the ground, it is collected in a 5-foot-deep pool. The area is difficult terrain, and any target that enters the area or starts its turn there must make a Strength saving throw, taking 5d6 bludgeoning damage and getting pulled 10 feet toward the center, taking half damage and not being pulled on a success.</p>\n<p>Boats can be pulled along by the current, and use the pilot&rsquo;s vehicle tool checks to resist the movement; boats do not take the damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Cast at Higher Levels.</strong> The area increases by 10 feet and the damage increases by 1d6 for every slot level above 5th.</p>",
